# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#  NSE Stock Dashboard — backend environment template
#
#  Copy to backend/.env and fill in your values.
#  .env is in .gitignore — NEVER commit this file with real secrets.
#
#  On EC2: sensitive values are loaded from SSM Parameter Store automatically.
#  You only need STAGE set correctly on each EC2.
#
#  Precedence: env var → .env file → SSM Parameter Store
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Deployment stage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# staging → DynamoDB prefix "stg_", SSM path /nse/staging/, SQS nse-scraping-jobs-staging
# prod    → no prefix,              SSM path /nse/prod/,    SQS nse-scraping-jobs
#
# Local dev: use staging (points at staging DynamoDB tables — safe to experiment)
# Staging EC2: /opt/nse-staging/.env has STAGE=staging
# Prod EC2:    /opt/nse/.env          has STAGE=prod
STAGE=staging

# ── App ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
APP_ENV=development
DEBUG=true

# ── JWT Authentication ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate:  python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
# On EC2:    leave empty — loaded from SSM /nse/{stage}/jwt-secret
SECRET_KEY=replace-with-your-own-secret-key

ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440

# ── AWS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EC2 uses the instance profile (NSEStockDashboardEC2Role) — no keys needed.
# For local dev: run  aws configure  with your IAM user credentials.
AWS_REGION=ap-south-1
AWS_ACCOUNT_ID=YOUR_AWS_ACCOUNT_ID
S3_ASSETS_BUCKET=nse-assets-YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID

# ── Amazon SQS (scraping job queue) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# On EC2: leave empty — loaded from SSM /nse/{stage}/sqs-jobs-url
# Local dev: leave empty → uses in-memory queue (no AWS needed)
SQS_SCRAPING_JOBS_URL=

# ── Amazon SNS (operational alerts) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# On EC2: leave empty — loaded from SSM
SNS_ALERTS_ARN=

# ── Amazon Comprehend (ML sentiment scoring) ──────────────────────────────────
# true  → ML via Comprehend (free: 50k units/month for 12 months)
# false → keyword-only scoring (no AWS calls, works fully offline)
COMPREHEND_ENABLED=false

# ── Email / SMTP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# On EC2: leave empty — loaded from SSM
GMAIL_USER=
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=
